The '''Code of Safe Working Practices''' (COSWP) is published by the [[Maritime and Coastguard Agency]] (MCA) of the [[UK]]. The code details the regulatory framework for [[health and safety]] aboard [[ship]], safety management and statutory duties underlying to the advice in the code and the areas that should be covered when introducing a new recruit to safety procedures on board.<ref>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/code-of-safe-working-practices-for-merchant-seafarers</ref>

The code arose from the Health and Safety at Work act (1974).

